The paper discusses the construction of codes for network coding, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of combinatorial designs and subspace codes also suggests a connection to distributed systems (cs.DS) and coding theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper mentions the decoding process, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
